                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "locations",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Locations",
                    "image": "Sidebar_3_Locations.png"
                },
                {
                    "name": "Kitharodian Academy (Taldor)",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": ": Famed bardic college teaching students of all social classes. <br/><b>Magaambya (Nantambu)</b>: Ancient school with some of the world's greatest stores of arcane knowledge. <br/><b>University of Lepidstadt (Ustalav)</b>: School primarily focusing on alchemy, medicine, and scientific study.",
                    "sources": {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 240",
                            "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 240",
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                        },
                        "page": 240
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "Uncommon Scholastic Disciplines",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "Beside the life and natural sciences such as arcana, biology, botany, geology, oceanography, and zoology, demand is increasing in cities for more modern disciplines, like anthropology, economics, sociology, urban planning, and even art curation and forensic investigation.",
                    "sources": {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 240",
                            "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 240",
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                        },
                        "page": 240
                    },
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                }
            ],
            "text": "True power comes from knowledge: the power to shape the growth of kingdoms by mere whispers, staying three steps ahead of adversaries, or even knowing which flora is best for creating untraceable poisons.",
            "sources": {
                "type": "source",
                "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
